%S A396409 0,0,1,0,3,1,2,0,5,3,4,1,6,2,3,0,7,5,6,3,8,4,5,1,10,6,7,2,9,3,4,0,9,7,
%T A396409 8,5,10,6,7,3,12,8,9,4,11,5,6,1,14,10,11,6,13,7,8,2,15,9,10,3,12,4,5,
%U A396409 0,11,9,10,7,12,8,9,5,14,10,11,6,13,7,8,3,16,12,13,8,15,9,10,4,17,11,12,5
%N A396409 Number of iterations of x -> x XOR 2^A000120(x) from x = n to reach a number of the form 2^m-1.
%C A396409 A number x with n 1s has at most two preimages: x XOR 2^(n-1) if the (n-1)-th bit of x is 1, and x XOR 2^(n+1) if (n+1)-th bit of x is 0.
%C A396409 The directed graph induced on the natural numbers by this mapping is a binary tree, with a root at infinity and a 'stem' of numbers of the form 2^m-1. This sequence measures the distance to the stem.
%C A396409 Compare this to A326730 (from x -> x XOR 2^(A000120(x)-1)), measuring distance to 0 (which all elements eventually hit); this map acts on 2*n as A326730's acts on n.
%C A396409 The maximum a(n) for n in the range [0..2^l] is binomial(l,2), achieved by n=A233411(l).
%C A396409 Sum_{n=0..2^l-1} a(n)   = 2^(l-2)*(l^2 - 3*l + 4) - 1.
%C A396409 Sum_{n=0..2^l-1} a(n)^2 = 2^(l-4)*(3*l^4 - 14*l^3 + 57*l^2 - 166*l + 240)/3 - 5.
%C A396409 Thus, the waiting time for an n uniformly sampled in [0..2^l) has expectation l*(l-3)/4 + 1 - 1/2^l, and variance l*(l+1)*(l+1/2)/12 - 2*l + 4 + O(l^2/2^l).
%C A396409 If n is written as the binary word 1^(o_0) 0^(z_0) 1^(o_1) ... (ignoring the last run of trailing 1s for odd n), then (with O_i = Sum_{j=0..i} o_j), a(n) = Sum_i 2*O_i*z_i - o_i.
%H A396409 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A396409/b396409.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..8191</a>
%F A396409 a(2*n+1) = a(n), a(2*n) = a(n) + wt(n) + wt(n+1) - 1 = a(n) + 2*wt(n) - val2(n+1), where wt=A000120 and val2=A007814 (val2(n+1) is n's number of trailing 1s in binary).
%F A396409 a(2*n) = A326730(n).
